<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ870506-0166 </DOCNO><HL> Banner Industries Inc. SellsRail Unit for $15.5 Million</HL><DD> 05/06/87</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> BNR OAKTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> CLEVELAND  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Banner Industries Inc. said it completed the sale of Railway Maintenance Equipment Co. to Oak Industries Inc. for $15.5 million.    Milwaukee, Wis.-based Railway Maintenance, a division of Banner's Rexnord Inc. subsidiary, had 1986 sales of $16 million and it employs 100 people. The sale is part of a program to shed several Rexnord businesses representing about $200 million in net assets.    Banner is a motor-freight carrier and a maker of aircraft replacement parts. San Diego-based Oak produces electronic parts and controls, and it makes equipment for cable-television-system operators. </TEXT></DOC>